README Before creating the template
-----------------------------------
Requrements:
- Centos7


Configuration:
- This vm should have the access through the client/Master VM.
- Copy the id_rsa.pub key contents from client/master to this VM's ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

  Example :
  ========================================================================================== 
	msys@msys-ThinkPad-Edge-E431:~/projects/vdbench/vdbench-repo$ ssh-keygen -t rsa 
	Generating public/private rsa key pair. 
	Enter file in which to save the key (/home/msys/.ssh/id_rsa):  
	Enter passphrase (empty for no passphrase):  
	Enter same passphrase again:  
	Your identification has been saved in /home/msys/.ssh/id_rsa. 
	Your public key has been saved in /home/msys/.ssh/id_rsa.pub. 
	The key fingerprint is: 
	SHA256:5vY5tKHpRuUhIAiQQBpq7OneERpFWWV4qT82D39Ydas msys@msys-ThinkPad-Edge-E431 
	The key's randomart image is: 
	+---[RSA 2048]----+ 
	|O+ oo.oo.        | 
	|=.o...oo         | 
	|oo . .o.         | 
	|o o  .  . o  . . | 
	| + .  . S+ .. . .| 
	|. o .  O. +.   . | 
	| o .  ..O+oo  .  | 
	|. . .  .+=oo E   | 
	| . .   o. +.     | 
	+----[SHA256]-----+ 
	msys@msys-ThinkPad-Edge-E431:~/projects/vdbench/vdbench-repo$ sudo apt-get install sshpass 
	msys@msys-ThinkPad-Edge-E431:~/projects/vdbench/vdbench-repo$ sshpass -p 'master#123' ssh root@192.168.102.13 'mkdir -p ~/.ssh' 
	msys@msys-ThinkPad-Edge-E431:~/projects/vdbench/vdbench-repo$ cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub | sshpass -p 'master#123' ssh root@192.168.102.13 'cat >> /root/.ssh/authorized_keys' 
	msys@msys-ThinkPad-Edge-E431:~/projects/vdbench/vdbench-repo$ sshpass -p 'master#123' ssh root@192.168.102.13 'chmod 700 ~/.ssh; chmod 640 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys' 
  ========================================================================================== 

- Every VM created from this template should send the IP address to the FTP server.
- Run cron job to send the IP address.

  Example :
  ========================================================================================== 
	[root@localhost ~]# cat /etc/cron.d/qnap-onboot1  
	@reboot root if ! [ -f /root/donotdelete ]; then sleep 40; echo `hostname -I | cut -d" " -f 1` | sshpass -p 'master#123' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@192.168.102.13 "cat >> /qnap-vm.txt"; touch /root/donotdelete; fi &>>/tmp/qnap-cronjob-error-log
  ========================================================================================== 
